{
  "stem": "2581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I felt grown up that I, you know, steal that sort of a sip of wine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At home, we spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But of course, we went to a Polish school and we spoke perfect Polish, my father being an officer in the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had many-- rather most-- Gentile customers, so we would speak-- my father would speak Polish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother also.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, she went to school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everyone went to school, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every Friday night, we would go to a Hevrah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In this small town, we had a large synagogue, a beautiful, beautiful synagogue that the Germans had turned into-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] what did they turn it into?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They kept the horses there-- a barn.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Poles have now a firehouse made out of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had this beautiful, tremendous synagogue where my grandfather would pray.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father-- And then there was a [NON-ENGLISH], Hasidic [NON-ENGLISH], and it was Alexander, and I think there was another one.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father belonged to a Hevrah, that was mostly partisans, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Artisans.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Artisans.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I keep thinking-- artisans, were, you know, tailors, and shoemakers, and other people like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father would pray before the congregation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's called a [NON-ENGLISH], but I think he liked to be called a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He sang beautiful songs, beautiful melodies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Modern melodies, but older prayers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was every Friday night, we would go to that synagogue and bring home a guest, that was called a [NON-ENGLISH] for dinner.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There wasn't a Friday that my father wouldn't take home someone, you know, that would come to the city as-- those people that are wandering from town to town, they stopped for Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
